  "intent_precise": "Promega MagneHis\u2122 Protein Purification System: Using magblock (deep_well_plate, slot 2), 12-channel reservoir (reservoir, slot 2), 3-channel reservoir (reservoir, slot 3), PCR plate for elution (plate, slot 4). With magnetic module. (1) Pause: Replace 300\u00b5l tipracks in slots 5-11 before resuming. (2) Transfer 150\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (3) Transfer 250\u00b5L from source to destination. (4) Transfer 50\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (5) Incubate for 10 minutes. (6) Engage magnets at 14.94mm height for bead separation. (7) Incubate for 5 minutes. (8) Transfer 1.5mL from source A1 to destination A1. (9) Disengage magnets to release beads. (10) Transfer 300\u00b5L from source to destination. (11) Mix 3 times at 150\u00b5L. (12) Engage magnets at 14.94mm height for bead separation. (13) Incubate for 2 minutes. (14) Transfer 300\u00b5L from source A1 to waste_set A1. (15) Disengage magnets to release beads. (16) Transfer 150\u00b5L from source to destination. (17) Mix 3 times at 120\u00b5L. (18) Engage magnets at 14.94mm height for bead separation. (19) Incubate for 2 minutes. (20) Transfer 150\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (21) Disengage magnets to release beads.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation. (volumes 30\u00b5L-1.5mL, ~20 min total)",
  "intent": "For this Promega MagneHis\u2122 protein purification, start by setting up your deck with the magblock deep well plate in slot 2, reservoirs in slots 2 and 3, and your PCR elution plate in slot 4, then pause to replace the 300\u00b5l tipracks in slots 5-11 before beginning the transfers. Begin by adding 150\u00b5L, then 250\u00b5L, followed by 50\u00b5L to well A1, incubate for 10 minutes, then engage the magnets at 14.94mm height and hold for 5 minutes for bead separation. Continue with the wash steps by adding 1.5mL, mixing 3 times at 150\u00b5L after disengaging magnets, re-engaging magnets for 2 minutes, then removing 300\u00b5L to waste, followed by a final wash with 150\u00b5L, mixing 3 times at 120\u00b5L, magnetic separation for 2 minutes, and transferring the final 150\u00b5L to your elution plate. Remember to disengage the magnets after each separation step to release the beads before the next transfer.",
